cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR 

This paper focuses on the development of a deep learning-based vision system for robotic harvesting of fruits in apple orchards. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. The use of deep learning also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of RGB-D images and 3D visualisation, which could suggest a potential fit with the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
